(121, 5, 1, '', '2014-11-06 00:24:01', 262, 6164, '54001a43927c8a65d51c21d38e0fbddc15cf99df', '{\"id\":5,\"asset_id\":\"64\",\"title\":\"Setup environment work of Sencha Touch 2.3.1\",\"alias\":\"setup-environment-work-of-sencha-touch\",\"introtext\":\"<h2 id=\\\"getting_started-section-required-software\\\">Required Software<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n<li>Download and unzip <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.sencha.com\\/products\\/touch\\/download\\\">Sencha Touch<\\/a>. You can unzip the software to any directory.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Sencha Touch requires <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/chrome\\\">Chrome<\\/a> or <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.apple.com\\/safari\\\">Safari<\\/a> for good view<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.sencha.com\\/products\\/sencha-cmd\\/download\\\">Sencha Cmd<\\/a>.<br \\/> Sencha Touch 2.3.1 requires Sencha Cmd 4.0.1, 4.0.2, or later. To check that you have correctly installed Sencha Cmd, type the sencha command, for example:\\r\\n<pre><em>sencha<\\/em><\\/pre>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oracle.com\\/technetwork\\/java\\/javase\\/downloads\\/jre7-downloads-1880261.html\\\">Java Runtime Environment<\\/a> version 1.7. Sencha Cmd is written in Java and needs the JRE to run. <strong>Note<\\/strong>: If you are building an Android app using Windows, you must install the <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oracle.com\\/technetwork\\/java\\/javase\\/downloads\\/jdk7-downloads-1880260.html\\\">Java SDK<\\/a>. You can build an iOS app under Windows with the JRE, but not an Android app<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ruby-lang.org\\/en\\/downloads\\/\\\">Ruby<\\/a> to create the compiled CSS used by Touch.<br \\/> <br \\/> <strong>Windows <\\/strong>=&gt; Download Ruby from <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/rubyinstaller.org\\/downloads\\/\\\">rubyinstaller.org<\\/a>. Download the RubyInstaller .exe file and run it.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<h2 id=\\\"getting_started-section-installation\\\">Installation<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Extract the Sencha Touch download zip file, which can be in any directory.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Start your web server such as <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.apachefriends.org\\/en\\/xampp.html\\\">XAMPP<\\/a> , create an app directory where your web server expects to find apps ( &lt;XAMPP_install_dir&gt;\\/htdocs directory )<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 id=\\\"getting_started-section-generating-your-first-app\\\">Generating Your First App<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Now that you have Sencha Touch and Sencha Cmd installed, you can generate an application.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>With Window, Open cmd and run command:<\\/p>\\r\\n<pre id=\\\"ext-gen1454\\\"><em>sencha -sdk \\/path\\/to\\/touch generate app NameApp \\/path\\/to\\/myapp  <\\/em><\\/pre>\\r\\n<p>Where:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n<li><em>\\/path\\/to\\/touch<\\/em> is the directory where you unzipped the Touch software.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><em>NameApp <\\/em>is the name you give your application.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\",\"fulltext\":\"\\r\\n<p>You can verify if your application has generated successfully by opening it in a web browser , navigate to http:\\/\\/localhost\\/<em>NameApp<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Note<\\/strong>: This is guide for Sencha touch 2.3.1 on window and XAMPP server<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 id=\\\"getting_started-section-explore-the-code\\\">Explore the Code<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The following listing provides a short description of each file and directory, the complete list of the generated files can be found in the <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/docs.sencha.com\\/touch\\/2.3.1\\/#%21\\/guide\\/command\\\">Sencha Cmd<\\/a> documentation:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li><strong>app<\\/strong> - The directory containing the Models, Views, Controllers, and Stores for your app.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>app.js<\\/strong> - The main JavaScript entry point for your app.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>app.json<\\/strong> - The configuration file for your app.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>index.html<\\/strong> - The HTML file for your app.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>packager.json<\\/strong> - The configuration file used by Sencha Cmd for creating native packages for your application.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>resources<\\/strong> - The directory containing the CSS and the images for your app<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Open app.js, the main entry point for your app, in your editor.The <em>launch<\\/em> function is the entry point to your application.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"apps\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Demo Datepicker with sencha <\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>&nbsp;For more detail when build basic apps with sencha touch, please read following link&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/docs.sencha.com\\/touch\\/2.3.1\\/#!\\/guide\\/first_app\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">http:\\/\\/docs.sencha.com\\/touch\\/2.3.1\\/#!\\/guide\\/first_app<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"state\":1,\"catid\":\"12\",\"created\":\"2014-05-02 16:08:00\",\"created_by\":\"262\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2014-11-06 00:24:01\",\"modified_by\":\"262\",\"checked_out\":\"262\",\"checked_out_time\":\"2014-11-06 00:20:58\",\"publish_up\":\"2014-06-09 16:08:00\",\"publish_down\":\"0000-00-00 00:00:00\",\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":false,\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":false,\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":false,\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_icons\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_print_icon\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_email_icon\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_vote\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":21,\"ordering\":\"0\",\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":\"1\",\"hits\":\"365\",\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"xreference\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', 0);
